{"prompt": "How to extract structured data using JSON-LD in WebQL?\n\nInput: Extract product information from JSON-LD script tags\n\nGenerate a WebQL query:", "completion": "{\n  \"@url\": \"https://schema.org/Product\",\n  \"@steps\": [\n    {\n      \"@json-ld\": {\n        \"@schema\": \"Product\",\n        \"@fields\": [\"name\", \"description\", \"brand\", \"offers\", \"image\"]\n      },\n      \"@name\": \"product_data\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"@json-ld\": {\n        \"@all-schemas\": true\n      },\n      \"@name\": \"all_structured_data\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"@json-ld\": {\n        \"@schema\": \"Organization\",\n        \"@fields\": [\"name\", \"address\", \"contactPoint\", \"url\"]\n      },\n      \"@name\": \"organization_info\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}
{"prompt": "Create WebQL with conditional logic based on page content\n\nInput: Extract different data depending on what elements exist on the page\n\nGenerate a WebQL query:", "completion": "{\n  \"@url\": \"https://quotes.toscrape.com/\",\n  \"@steps\": [\n    {\n      \"@xpath\": \"//div[@class='quote']\",\n      \"@fields\": {\n        \"text\": \".//span[@class='text']/text()\",\n        \"author\": \".//small[@class='author']/text()\",\n        \"tags\": \".//div[@class='tags']//a/text()\"\n      },\n      \"@follow\": {\n        \"@xpath\": \".//small[@class='author']//a/@href\",\n        \"@steps\": [\n          {\n            \"@if\": {\n              \"@exists\": \".author-born-date\"\n            },\n            \"@then\": [\n              {\n                \"@xpath\": \"//div[@class='author-details']\",\n                \"@fields\": {\n                  \"name\": \".//h3[@class='author-title']/text()\",\n                  \"birth_date\": \".//span[@class='author-born-date']/text()\",\n                  \"birth_location\": \".//span[@class='author-born-location']/text()\",\n                  \"description\": \".//div[@class='author-description']/text()\"\n                }\n              }\n            ],\n            \"@else\": [\n              {\n                \"@xpath\": \"//div[@class='author-details']\",\n                \"@fields\": {\n                  \"name\": \".//h3[@class='author-title']/text()\",\n                  \"description\": \".//div[@class='author-description']/text()\",\n                  \"note\": \"'No birth information available'\"\n                }\n              }\n            ]\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"}
{"prompt": "Write WebQL for comprehensive blog article extraction\n\nInput: Extract blog posts with full content following\n\nGenerate a WebQL query:", "completion": "{\n  \"@url\": \"https://blog.ycombinator.com/\",\n  \"@steps\": [\n    {\n      \"@xpath\": \"//article | //div[contains(@class, 'post')]\",\n      \"@fields\": {\n        \"title\": \".//h1//text() | .//h2//text() | .//h3//text()\",\n        \"excerpt\": \".//p[1]/text() | .//div[contains(@class, 'excerpt')]/text()\",\n        \"date\": \".//time/@datetime | .//span[contains(@class, 'date')]/text()\",\n        \"author\": \".//span[contains(@class, 'author')]/text() | .//div[contains(@class, 'byline')]//a/text()\",\n        \"read_more_link\": \".//a[contains(@class, 'read-more')]/@href | .//h1/a/@href | .//h2/a/@href\"\n      },\n      \"@follow\": {\n        \"@xpath\": \".//a[contains(@class, 'read-more')]/@href | .//h1/a/@href | .//h2/a/@href\",\n        \"@steps\": [\n          {\n            \"@xpath\": \"//article | //main | //div[@id='content'] | //div[contains(@class, 'post-content')]\",\n            \"@fields\": {\n              \"headline\": \".//h1/text()\",\n              \"full_content\": \"string-join(.//p//text(), ' ')\",\n              \"publish_date\": \".//time/@datetime | .//meta[@property='article:published_time']/@content\",\n              \"author_name\": \".//span[contains(@class, 'author')]/text() | .//meta[@name='author']/@content\",\n              \"categories\": \".//div[contains(@class, 'categories')]//a/text() | .//meta[@property='article:section']/@content\",\n              \"featured_image\": \".//img[1]/@src | .//meta[@property='og:image']/@content\"\n            }\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"}
{"prompt": "How to use multiple XPath alternatives in WebQL?\n\nInput: Extract data with fallback selectors for different page structures\n\nGenerate a WebQL query:", "completion": "Use the pipe (|) operator for XPath alternatives in WebQL:\n\n\"title\": \".//h1//text() | .//h2//text() | .//h3//text()\"\n\"date\": \".//time/@datetime | .//span[contains(@class, 'date')]/text()\"\n\"content\": \".//div[@class='content']//text() | .//article//p//text()\"\n\nThis tries each XPath in order until one matches, providing fallback options for different page layouts."}
{"prompt": "What are WebQL conditional statements?\n\nInput: Explain @if, @then, @else in WebQL\n\nGenerate a WebQL query:", "completion": "WebQL supports conditional extraction with @if, @then, @else:\n\n{\n  \"@if\": {\n    \"@exists\": \".price-sale\"  // Check if element exists\n  },\n  \"@then\": [\n    // Extract sale price data\n    {\"@xpath\": \".//span[@class='sale-price']\", \"@fields\": {...}}\n  ],\n  \"@else\": [\n    // Extract regular price data\n    {\"@xpath\": \".//span[@class='regular-price']\", \"@fields\": {...}}\n  ]\n}\n\nConditions can check:\n- @exists: Element existence\n- @text-contains: Text content\n- @attribute-equals: Attribute values"}
